public class IRObject
extends DataElement

IRObject represents one document in the collection. It is used heavily in building the index.

printMarkupData

public void printMarkupData(java.lang.StringBuffer data,
                            DataElement theDE,
                            int id)
This method returns a string of markup data. In C++ this method is void and uses a char* to get the data back. Java doesn't do that so the char* becomes a StringBuffer and the result comes back in the StringBuffer.

The C++ API uses GetAsMarkup() to initialise the char* and return the string to the caller. I've made this method private and reworked getAsMarkup().

Parameters:
data - The StringBuffer that the result comes back in.
theDE - The dataelement to start with.
id - I can't find any use for this parameter in the C++.
